That's still cheating, isn't it?

567
00:28:48,420 --> 00:28:49,260
No, I...

568
00:28:49,260 --> 00:28:50,500
I broke up with Zheng Hao.

569
00:28:50,500 --> 00:28:51,980
I broke up with him

570
00:28:51,980 --> 00:28:53,740
before I got together with Shi Ye.

571
00:28:55,740 --> 00:28:57,100
You broke up long ago?

572
00:28:57,100 --> 00:28:59,740
No wonder you kept finding excuses

573
00:28:59,740 --> 00:29:01,660
when I suggested
meeting Zheng Hao.

574
00:29:01,740 --> 00:29:03,180
So you'd already broken up.

575
00:29:03,420 --> 00:29:05,100
Why didn't you tell me?

576
00:29:06,260 --> 00:29:09,260
I was afraid you'd be angry.

577
00:29:13,220 --> 00:29:14,740
So, what does Shi Ye do?

578
00:29:20,220 --> 00:29:21,260
He's a stand-up comedian.

579
00:29:21,660 --> 00:29:22,500
A what?

580
00:29:23,220 --> 00:29:24,740
A stand-up comedian.

581
00:29:25,020 --> 00:29:27,740
It's someone who tells jokes on stage.

582
00:29:27,740 --> 00:29:29,500
Like a crosstalk performer.

583
00:29:30,500 --> 00:29:31,940
What organization does he work for?

584
00:29:32,500 --> 00:29:33,500
Where does he work?

585
00:29:34,740 --> 00:29:37,180
He doesn't have a fixed workplace
or a stable position.

586
00:29:37,460 --> 00:29:39,740
Then where does he pay
his social insurance?

587
00:29:40,220 --> 00:29:41,560
He doesn't have social insurance.

588
00:29:42,100 --> 00:29:44,980
Then where does he perform?

589
00:29:46,500 --> 00:29:47,340
In a bar.

590
00:29:47,940 --> 00:29:48,780
What?

591
00:29:49,740 --> 00:29:50,980
In a bar.

592
00:29:54,500 --> 00:29:56,100
So he's just a drifter, isn't he?

593
00:29:57,020 --> 00:29:58,900
No, how could he be a drifter?

594
00:29:58,900 --> 00:30:00,460
If not, then what is he?

595
00:30:00,460 --> 00:30:03,020
Who performs in bars at night?

596
00:30:03,020 --> 00:30:05,660
Stand-up comedy
is a legitimate profession.

597
00:30:05,940 --> 00:30:06,780
I...

598
00:30:08,100 --> 00:30:09,460
A legitimate profession?

599
00:30:17,660 --> 00:30:19,260
For a man like this,

600
00:30:19,260 --> 00:30:20,940
you broke up with Zheng Hao?

601
00:30:22,220 --> 00:30:24,500
It wasn't for him
that I broke up with Zheng Hao.

602
00:30:24,500 --> 00:30:25,500
Have some water.

603
00:30:30,980 --> 00:30:33,260
(Shi Ye: Can't make the commercial gig.
You go ahead.)

604
00:30:33,260 --> 00:30:34,900
I'm off to work, Mom.

605
00:30:39,100 --> 00:30:40,180
I'm leaving, Mom.

606
00:31:25,740 --> 00:31:27,260
Smoking isn't allowed here.

607
00:31:47,660 --> 00:31:48,740
Is it Zheng Hao?

608
00:31:49,900 --> 00:31:50,740
I'm Xiuya's mother.

609
00:31:58,260 --> 00:31:59,100
Auntie?

610
00:32:00,500 --> 00:32:01,340
Auntie.

611
00:32:03,020 --> 00:32:04,900
I'm so sorry.
I've been in meetings all day

612
00:32:04,900 --> 00:32:06,740
and super busy. I didn't have much time.

613
00:32:10,180 --> 00:32:11,260
What brings you here?

614
00:32:12,740 --> 00:32:13,980
Oh, nothing.

615
00:32:16,660 --> 00:32:18,100
I already told you on the phone.

616
00:32:18,500 --> 00:32:19,740
I just wanted to see you.

617
00:32:21,220 --> 00:32:24,260
Here, take this hometown specialty.

618
00:32:24,740 --> 00:32:27,100
Auntie, you should keep it.

619
00:32:27,100 --> 00:32:27,980
I can't accept this.

620
00:32:28,740 --> 00:32:30,260
Why not?

621
00:32:31,660 --> 00:32:32,740
This is supposed to...

622
00:32:35,660 --> 00:32:39,260
I was planning
to meet your parents this time

623
00:32:39,940 --> 00:32:41,740
to discuss your wedding with Ya.

624
00:32:43,500 --> 00:32:44,940
But this child...

625
00:32:49,100 --> 00:32:49,940
This child...

626
00:32:49,940 --> 00:32:51,740
Auntie, please don't be upset.

627
00:32:51,740 --> 00:32:52,660
I'll accept it.

628
00:32:55,460 --> 00:32:56,300
Take it.

629
00:32:56,940 --> 00:32:57,780
Auntie,

630
00:32:58,260 --> 00:32:59,260
does Xiuya know

631
00:32:59,980 --> 00:33:01,020
you're here?

632
00:33:02,260 --> 00:33:03,100
She doesn't.

633
00:33:03,940 --> 00:33:05,900
I don't want to go up and let her know.

634
00:33:07,260 --> 00:33:08,900
I just want to tell you

635
00:33:10,500 --> 00:33:12,460
that I just found out you two broke up.

636
00:33:15,740 --> 00:33:17,500
She never told me.

637
00:33:18,500 --> 00:33:21,900
She must feel she's in the wrong,

638
00:33:22,660 --> 00:33:23,500
so

639
00:33:25,370 --> 00:33:26,940
she doesn't dare tell me.

640
00:33:29,500 --> 00:33:31,740
Auntie, you don't need to comfort me.

641
00:33:32,980 --> 00:33:34,660
Xiuya is happy now,

642
00:33:34,940 --> 00:33:37,260
so breaking up was the right decision.

643
00:33:37,260 --> 00:33:38,740
How could she be happy?

644
00:33:39,740 --> 00:33:41,220
Is Xu Yunfeng not treating her well?

645
00:33:41,500 --> 00:33:42,340
Xu Yunfeng?

646
00:33:44,420 --> 00:33:45,260
Who's that?

647
00:33:46,260 --> 00:33:47,660
Xiuya's boyfriend.

648
00:33:50,620 --> 00:33:52,260
I don't know his name.

649
00:33:52,650 --> 00:33:53,940
But that doesn't matter.

650
00:33:55,740 --> 00:33:56,980
What I want to say is,

651
00:33:58,100 --> 00:34:01,660
if Ya realizes her mistake

652
00:34:02,460 --> 00:34:03,900
and apologizes to you,

653
00:34:04,420 --> 00:34:05,740
will you forgive her?

654
00:34:16,380 --> 00:34:18,220
Auntie, my meeting

655
00:34:18,500 --> 00:34:19,980
isn't over yet.

656
00:34:19,990 --> 00:34:21,590
They're rushing me. I need to go.

657
00:34:23,730 --> 00:34:25,220
Just hear me out.

658
00:34:25,500 --> 00:34:28,020
Ya was just confused for a moment.

659
00:34:28,180 --> 00:34:29,500
If she breaks up with you,

660
00:34:29,500 --> 00:34:31,220
she'll regret it
for the rest of her life.

661
00:34:31,360 --> 00:34:33,620
I don't want her to live with regret.

662
00:34:33,980 --> 00:34:34,820
So,

663
00:34:35,980 --> 00:34:39,220
what are you thinking? Tell me.

664
00:34:39,620 --> 00:34:41,020
I'm on your side.

665
00:34:41,620 --> 00:34:42,460
Auntie,

666
00:34:43,500 --> 00:34:45,140
I just want Xiuya to be happy.

667
00:34:45,500 --> 00:34:48,300
I have to go now.

668
00:34:48,500 --> 00:34:51,140
I need to go to the meeting.

669
00:34:58,940 --> 00:35:00,700
Auntie, what brings you here?

670
00:35:02,140 --> 00:35:02,980
Who are you?

671
00:35:03,140 --> 00:35:04,620
I'm Xiuya's colleague.

672
00:35:04,620 --> 00:35:06,700
We've met by the elevator before,
remember?

673
00:35:07,980 --> 00:35:09,940
I guess I'm her former colleague now.

674
00:35:10,700 --> 00:35:12,300
Former colleague? Why?

675
00:35:12,500 --> 00:35:13,700
She resigned.

676
00:35:13,700 --> 00:35:15,460
So I'm her former colleague now, right?

677
00:35:15,460 --> 00:35:16,300
What?

678
00:35:17,900 --> 00:35:19,300
Xiuya resigned?

679
00:35:19,300 --> 00:35:20,980
Yeah, you didn't know?

680
00:35:20,980 --> 00:35:23,100
No way. Did she quit on her own?

681
00:35:23,700 --> 00:35:25,700
She resigned to pursue stand-up comedy.

682
00:35:25,940 --> 00:35:28,220
Besides, she doesn't need to work now.

683
00:35:28,500 --> 00:35:30,220
Of course she needs to work!

684
00:35:30,700 --> 00:35:33,220
- This...
- She...

685
00:35:38,140 --> 00:35:39,940
Can you take me to meet your manager?

686
00:35:40,300 --> 00:35:41,700
Sure, come with me?

687
00:35:41,700 --> 00:35:42,540
Sure.

688
00:35:43,420 --> 00:35:44,260
Let's go.

689
00:35:54,500 --> 00:35:56,100
Is this the kind of proposal you turn in

690
00:35:56,180 --> 00:35:57,700
after preparing for a whole week?

691
00:35:58,100 --> 00:35:59,900
Look at this rubbish.

692
00:35:59,960 --> 00:36:01,540
You used to finish this in three days.

693
00:36:01,540 --> 00:36:03,220
Now it takes over a week?

694
00:36:03,820 --> 00:36:05,700
That's because Wu Xiuya used to be here.

695
00:36:05,700 --> 00:36:07,220
How can you say that out loud?

696
00:36:07,380 --> 00:36:09,700
Now you know how good she is?

697
00:36:10,140 --> 00:36:10,980
Manager Hu.

698
00:36:11,460 --> 00:36:12,680
He Xiaoli, what's the matter?

699
00:36:13,500 --> 00:36:16,220
Manager Hu, I'm Xiuya's mother.

700
00:36:20,620 --> 00:36:21,460
Hello.

701
00:36:23,300 --> 00:36:24,140
Please, have a seat.

702
00:36:27,060 --> 00:36:27,900
Why stand there?

703
00:36:32,700 --> 00:36:33,540
Hello.

704
00:36:36,180 --> 00:36:37,620
What is her mom doing here?

705
00:36:39,100 --> 00:36:40,540
Aside from asking for her job back,

706
00:36:40,540 --> 00:36:42,700
I can't think of another reason.

707
00:36:42,780 --> 00:36:44,620
Xiuya still needs this job?

708
00:36:44,860 --> 00:36:46,020
What are you saying?

709
00:36:46,020 --> 00:36:47,220
That can't be the reason.

710
00:36:48,180 --> 00:36:49,580
Right. Xu Yunfeng.

711
00:36:49,820 --> 00:36:51,620
He'll give her any job she wants.

712
00:36:51,620 --> 00:36:53,100
Listen to what you just said.

713
00:36:53,380 --> 00:36:55,320
With Xu Yunfeng around,
what job does she need?

714
00:36:55,380 --> 00:36:57,620
No, relying on a man isn't right.

715
00:36:59,620 --> 00:37:00,700
I can't hear it clearly.

716
00:37:02,020 --> 00:37:03,620
I'll go over there to hear.

717
00:37:06,100 --> 00:37:06,940
Wait for me.

718
00:37:11,500 --> 00:37:15,140
(Pang Jing: Xiuya,
do you know your mom is here to see Hu?)

719
00:37:20,300 --> 00:37:24,140
(Pang Jing: Xiuya,
do you know your mom is here to see Hu?)

720
00:37:27,700 --> 00:37:29,020
Xiuya

721
00:37:29,020 --> 00:37:30,140
may look gentle,

722
00:37:30,380 --> 00:37:31,820
but she's quite strong-willed.

723
00:37:31,820 --> 00:37:33,060
She's got a strong personality.

724
00:37:33,540 --> 00:37:34,540
You know that, right?

725
00:37:34,780 --> 00:37:36,460
She resigned on her own.

726
00:37:37,380 --> 00:37:40,060
It was her personal decision.

727
00:37:41,220 --> 00:37:43,540
That's because she was young
and impulsive.

728
00:37:44,180 --> 00:37:45,700
She regrets it now.

729
00:37:46,900 --> 00:37:47,780
Is that so?

730
00:37:47,780 --> 00:37:49,220
Of course.

731
00:37:50,300 --> 00:37:52,420
When she applied for this position,

732
00:37:52,420 --> 00:37:54,420
there were tests and interviews.

733
00:37:54,620 --> 00:37:56,700
It took her more than a month.

734
00:37:56,900 --> 00:37:58,020
She told me

735
00:37:58,020 --> 00:37:59,700
how competitive it was,

736
00:37:59,700 --> 00:38:01,060
with over 100 candidates,

737
00:38:01,060 --> 00:38:02,860
so she had to prepare well.

738
00:38:02,860 --> 00:38:04,900
She worked so hard to prepare.

739
00:38:05,220 --> 00:38:06,480
During Spring Festival at home,

740
00:38:06,480 --> 00:38:08,140
while everyone else
was watching the gala,

741
00:38:08,140 --> 00:38:09,620
she was still working...

742
00:38:09,620 --> 00:38:12,020
She's incredibly serious about her work.

743
00:38:12,300 --> 00:38:13,300
I know that.

744
00:38:13,580 --> 00:38:14,620
And honestly,

745
00:38:15,040 --> 00:38:16,620
I thought it was a shame that she left.

746
00:38:16,620 --> 00:38:17,620
Exactly.

747
00:38:17,700 --> 00:38:18,700
But...

748
00:38:19,300 --> 00:38:21,420
If Xiuya admits she was wrong

749
00:38:21,420 --> 00:38:24,820
and sincerely apologizes,

750
00:38:24,820 --> 00:38:26,820
could you give her another chance?

751
00:38:28,300 --> 00:38:30,140
She's truly a diligent worker.

752
00:38:44,020 --> 00:38:45,600
Mom, what are you doing? Let's go home.

753
00:38:45,610 --> 00:38:46,360
Manager, sorry.

754
00:38:46,360 --> 00:38:47,420
I'll take my mom home now.

755
00:38:47,420 --> 00:38:48,680
- It's okay.
- Mom, let's go.

756
00:38:48,680 --> 00:38:49,500
What are you doing?

757
00:38:49,500 --> 00:38:52,460
- Mom.
- I'm helping you get your job back.

758
00:38:53,020 --> 00:38:54,180
Just apologize to Manager Hu.

759
00:38:54,180 --> 00:38:55,820
Manager Hu isn't unreasonable.

760
00:38:55,820 --> 00:38:56,820
She's kind.

761
00:38:56,820 --> 00:38:58,100
She'll give you another chance.

762
00:38:58,100 --> 00:38:59,640
- Hurry up.
- Mom, what are you doing?

763
00:38:59,640 --> 00:39:00,520
Stop embarrassing me.

764
00:39:00,520 --> 00:39:01,540
Let's go.

765
00:39:01,780 --> 00:39:03,580
Who's embarrassing, you or me?

766
00:39:04,780 --> 00:39:05,860
She's Xiuya's mother, right?

767
00:39:05,860 --> 00:39:07,540
You quit your job
and didn't even tell me.

768
00:39:07,780 --> 00:39:09,240
Isn't it because you're embarrassed?

769
00:39:10,820 --> 00:39:12,220
You've ruined your future.

770
00:39:12,220 --> 00:39:13,180
Don't you realize that?

771
00:39:13,580 --> 00:39:15,300
How can you act
so self-righteous with me?

772
00:39:15,540 --> 00:39:17,140
Mom, stop it.

773
00:39:17,420 --> 00:39:19,020
Don't talk nonsense, alright?

774
00:39:19,020 --> 00:39:20,700
I'm not ashamed. I'm doing fine.

775
00:39:20,700 --> 00:39:22,220
I have my own job.

776
00:39:22,220 --> 00:39:23,700
You call that doing fine?

777
00:39:23,860 --> 00:39:25,540
You can't even afford your rent.

778
00:39:25,700 --> 00:39:27,100
What job do you have?

779
00:39:27,140 --> 00:39:28,220
Stand-up comedy.

780
00:39:29,020 --> 00:39:30,300
Is that even a job?

781
00:39:30,540 --> 00:39:32,340
No fixed workplace or social insurance.

782
00:39:32,460 --> 00:39:34,900
You've been brainwashed by that boy,
haven't you?

783
00:39:35,460 --> 00:39:37,220
You gave up a good job.

784
00:39:37,220 --> 00:39:39,300
You gave up a good boyfriend.

785
00:39:39,380 --> 00:39:40,140
What are you doing?

786
00:39:40,340 --> 00:39:42,220
Do you want to end up
as some aimless drifter?

787
00:39:42,220 --> 00:39:44,540
Do you think you've lived a good life?

788
00:39:44,700 --> 00:39:46,140
Do you have social insurance

789
00:39:46,220 --> 00:39:47,900
and a stable position you mentioned?

790
00:39:48,540 --> 00:39:49,540
By your own definition,

791
00:39:49,540 --> 00:39:51,420
you are an aimless drifter too.

792
00:39:51,420 --> 00:39:52,260
I...

793
00:39:52,940 --> 00:39:53,940
I made sacrifices

794
00:39:54,380 --> 00:39:55,220
for you

795
00:39:55,220 --> 00:39:56,580
and our family.

796
00:39:58,220 --> 00:40:01,140
Looks like it was all for nothing.

797
00:40:01,420 --> 00:40:04,340
Don't use your sacrifice
to manipulate me.

798
00:40:05,860 --> 00:40:07,140
Without you,

799
00:40:08,100 --> 00:40:10,140
would I have given up my job?

800
00:40:12,140 --> 00:40:13,700
I've lived more than half my life now,

801
00:40:13,700 --> 00:40:14,940
and I finally understand.

802
00:40:15,460 --> 00:40:17,580
A woman can live without anything,

803
00:40:18,100 --> 00:40:19,940
but she can't live without her work.

804
00:40:20,700 --> 00:40:22,540
That's the foundation of who you are.

805
00:40:22,700 --> 00:40:25,060
I've told you. I do have a job.

806
00:40:25,220 --> 00:40:26,220
What job?

807
00:40:26,220 --> 00:40:27,620
Stand-up comedy.

808
00:40:27,700 --> 00:40:29,100
Is that even a job?

809
00:40:29,140 --> 00:40:31,100
Why isn't it a job?

810
00:40:31,100 --> 00:40:33,540
Can it support you
and your little delinquent?

811
00:40:33,540 --> 00:40:35,900
He's not a delinquent,
his name is Shi Ye.

812
00:40:36,700 --> 00:40:39,540
Shi Ye? He's just nothing.

813
00:40:42,100 --> 00:40:45,700
Are you out of your mind?

814
00:40:51,700 --> 00:40:54,300
You've driven me so mad.

815
00:40:59,700 --> 00:41:03,220
Giving up a perfectly good job...

816
00:41:06,780 --> 00:41:08,860
(Xiuya looks at her colleagues
outside the door.)

817
00:41:09,220 --> 00:41:11,220
(They watch from a distance,
uninvolved.)

818
00:41:11,540 --> 00:41:12,700
(Some look conflicted.)

819
00:41:13,180 --> 00:41:14,320
(Some are recording videos.)

820
00:41:14,780 --> 00:41:16,340
(Some seem to pity her.)

821
00:41:16,700 --> 00:41:18,780
(Snickers and whispers)

822
00:41:19,100 --> 00:41:20,860
(sneak into her ears like snakes,)

823
00:41:20,860 --> 00:41:21,700
Don't do this.

824
00:41:21,700 --> 00:41:23,100
(devouring her dignity.)

825
00:41:23,340 --> 00:41:26,460
(Xiuya feels as if she's at the center
of a whirlpool,)

826
00:41:26,780 --> 00:41:29,700
(sinking deeper and deeper,
unable to stop.)

827
00:41:41,220 --> 00:41:42,180
Hurry and leave.

828
00:41:51,220 --> 00:41:54,860
(Zhonghe Group)

829
00:42:33,060 --> 00:42:38,140
(Wu Xiuya: Please call me back
as soon as possible.)

830
00:42:52,460 --> 00:42:54,180
What is this about now?

831
00:42:54,380 --> 00:42:55,220
I'm going back.

832
00:42:56,300 --> 00:42:57,860
There are no more high-speed trains.

833
00:42:58,100 --> 00:42:58,940
Don't worry about me.

834
00:43:07,060 --> 00:43:08,340
Don't leave. I'll go.

835
00:43:43,940 --> 00:43:47,100
Everyone in the company
is laughing at me.

836
00:43:47,380 --> 00:43:49,620
If you think about it
from your mom's perspective,

837
00:43:49,820 --> 00:43:51,900
don't you think she feels ashamed, too?

838
00:43:52,700 --> 00:43:53,860
But even if it's humiliating,

839
00:43:53,860 --> 00:43:55,460
she still wants you to go back to work.

840
00:43:55,460 --> 00:43:57,620
Because she believes it's best for you.

841
00:43:57,940 --> 00:43:59,220
Try to understand her more.

842
00:44:00,900 --> 00:44:02,140
Try to understand her.

843
